BEGIN_PGML Multiply [`2\sqrt{7}\cdot3\sqrt{21}\text{.}`]
[@KeyboardInstructions('To type [`\sqrt{\phantom{x}}\text{,}`] use [|sqrt( )|]*.')@]**
[_]{$answer}{10}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION First multiply the non-radical factors together and the radical factors together. Then look for further simplifications.
[```\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} 2\sqrt{7}\cdot3\sqrt{21}\amp=2\cdot3\cdot\sqrt{7}\cdot\sqrt{21}\\ \amp=6\cdot\sqrt{7}\cdot\sqrt{7\cdot3}\\ \amp=6\sqrt{49\cdot3}\\ \amp=6\cdot7\cdot\sqrt{3}\\ \amp=42\sqrt{3} \end{aligned} ```]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
